Browser-witness gm-method: a boolean element-presence witness (charts present, cards exist) passes while the page is still broken -- a client page that fetches relative API paths under a project subpath (GitHub Pages /<repo>/) must be witnessed by the ACTUAL network requests and resolved values, not DOM presence. Failure mode: deriving a base URL by stripping location.href works when tested at the final route but computes the wrong root during a transient SPA-routing/redirect state, yielding root-absolute /docs/api that 404s under the subpath. Remedy: source the canonical deployed base from embedded site config (the build emits the real deployed url), timing-independent, never from location.href path-stripping. Always witness subpath-deployed pages on the LIVE deployed URL after the Pages deploy completes, reading network request URLs + fetchError + real card values, since local-root serving masks the subpath bug.